      <title>Xenoestrogen</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/xenoestrogen/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 04 Nov 2025 04:25:00 -0500</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/xenoestrogen/</guid>
      <description>Any of a group of natural or synthetic compounds showing hormone-like activity that acts as an estrogen.</description>
      <content:encoded>&lt;div class=&#34;themed-dict-entry&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;font-size: large;&#34;&gt;Xenoestrogen&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;font-size: large;&#34;&gt;English&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;font-size: large;&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Part of Speech:&lt;/em&gt;‚ÄÉ|‚ÄÉ&#xA;    &lt;span style=&#34;white-space: nowrap;&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;strong&gt;IPA (RP &amp;amp; GenAm):&lt;/strong&gt; /Àåz…õn…ô äÀà…õstr…ôd í…ôn/ or /ÀåziÀêno äÀà…õstr…ôd í…ôn/&#xA;      &lt;button aria-label=&#34;Play pronunciation&#34; onclick=&#34;document.getElementById(&#39;xenoestrogen-audio&#39;).play()&#34; style=&#34;background: none; border: none; cursor: pointer; padding-left: 6px;&#34;&gt;&#xA;        üîä&#xA;      &lt;/button&gt;&#xA;      &lt;audio id=&#34;xenoestrogen-audio&#34; preload=&#34;none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;source src=&#34;https://example.com/pronunciations/xenoestrogen.mp3&#34; type=&#34;audio/mpeg&#34;&gt;&lt;/source&gt;&#xA;        Your browser does not support the audio element.&#xA;      &lt;/audio&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;font-size: large;&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rhymes:&lt;/strong&gt; -estrogen&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p style=&#34;color: #999999; font-style: italic;&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;font-size: large;&#34;&gt;‚ÄúAny of a group of natural or synthetic compounds showing hormone-like activity that acts as an estrogen.‚Äù&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;  &lt;hr /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;font-size: large;&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Definition:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&#xA;  Xenoestrogens are a diverse class of &lt;strong&gt;natural and artificial chemicals&lt;/strong&gt; that mimic or interfere with the function of the hormone &lt;em&gt;estrogen&lt;/em&gt;. They may bind to estrogen receptors, alter endocrine signaling, or disrupt normal reproductive development. Common sources include &lt;strong&gt;plastics&lt;/strong&gt; (e.g., BPA, phthalates), &lt;strong&gt;pesticides&lt;/strong&gt;, and certain &lt;strong&gt;industrial byproducts&lt;/strong&gt;.&#xA;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;separator&#34; style=&#34;clear: both; text-align: center;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;a href=&#34;https://example.com/images/xenoestrogen.png&#34; style=&#34;margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;img border=&#34;0&#34; src=&#34;https://example.com/images/xenoestrogen.png&#34; width=&#34;320&#34; alt=&#34;Illustration of xenoestrogen molecular structure&#34; /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;hr /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;font-size: large;&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example Sentence:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&#xA;  Wastewater-borne &lt;em&gt;xenoestrogens&lt;/em&gt; have been implicated in endocrine disruption across multiple species.&#xA;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;  &lt;hr /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;font-size: large;&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Etymology:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&#xA;  From Greek &lt;em&gt;xenos&lt;/em&gt; ‚Äúforeign‚Äù + &lt;em&gt;estrogen&lt;/em&gt; ‚Äî literally ‚Äúforeign estrogen.‚Äù&#xA;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;  &lt;hr /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;font-size: large;&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Related Terms:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;  &lt;ul style=&#34;font-size: large; list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 1.5em;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Phytoestrogen&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äî plant-derived estrogen-like compound.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Endocrine disruptor&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äî substance that interferes with hormonal systems.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hormone mimic&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äî molecule imitating natural hormone action.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;</content:encoded>
